---
import RedSectionHeader from "../common/RedSectionHeader.astro";
---

<section class="py-20 bg-gray-50" id="3a-vs-3b-comparison">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <RedSectionHeader
            title="Pillar 3a vs 3b: The Complete Comparison"
            className="mb-12"
        />

        <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-700 max-w-none">
            <p class="mb-12 text-xl leading-relaxed">
                The "3rd Pillar" is not a single account; it is split into two
                distinct systems: <strong>3a (Restricted/Gebundene)</strong> and <strong
                    >3b (Unrestricted/Freie)</strong
                >. Choosing the right one—or typically, the right combination of
                both—is crucial for balancing tax optimization with liquidity.
            </p>

            <!-- 5.1 Key Differences Explained -->
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 mb-16">
                <div
                    class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100"
                >
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
                        <div
                            class="bg-red-100 text-red-800 font-bold px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-xl"
                        >
                            3a
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 m-0">
                            Restricted Pension Plan
                        </h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-sm">
                        Think of 3a as a <strong
                            >"Tax-Optimized Locked Box."</strong
                        > The state gives you massive tax breaks in exchange for locking
                        your money away until retirement.
                    </p>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 mt-6 text-sm">
                        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                            <span class="text-green-500 font-bold">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Tax Deductible:</strong> Contributions reduce
                                taxable income 1:1.</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                            <span class="text-red-500 font-bold">✗</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Restricted Access:</strong> Funds locked
                                until 5 years before retirement (mostly).</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                            <span class="text-green-500 font-bold">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Forced Savings:</strong> Excellent discipline
                                for long-term wealth.</span
                            >
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div
                    class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100"
                >
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
                        <div
                            class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 font-bold px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-xl"
                        >
                            3b
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 m-0">
                            Unrestricted Pension Plan
                        </h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-sm">
                        Think of 3b as a <strong
                            >"Flexible Wealth Account."</strong
                        > You have freedom to withdraw anytime, but you lose the upfront
                        tax deduction.
                    </p>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 mt-6 text-sm">
                        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                            <span class="text-red-500 font-bold">✗</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>No Deduction:</strong> Contributions do not
                                reduce income tax (in most cantons).</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                            <span class="text-green-500 font-bold">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Total Freedom:</strong> Withdraw any amount,
                                at any time, for any reason.</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                            <span class="text-green-500 font-bold">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Uncapped:</strong> Invest as much as you
                                want (millions if you wish).</span
                            >
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 5.2 Tax Implications Deep Dive -->
            <div class="mb-16">
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                    Tax Implications: The Math
                </h3>
                <p>
                    The primary driver for Pillar 3a is tax efficiency. Let's
                    look at the numbers for a typical expat earning CHF 120,000
                    in Zurich.
                </p>

                <div class="overflow-x-auto my-8">
                    <table class="min-w-full bg-white border border-gray-200">
                        <thead class="bg-gray-100">
                            <tr>
                                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left"
                                    >Scenario (CHF 7,000 Contrib.)</th
                                >
                                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left">Pillar 3a</th>
                                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left">Pillar 3b</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200 text-sm">
                            <tr>
                                <td class="font-bold py-3 px-4"
                                    >Immediate Tax Saving</td
                                >
                                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-bold"
                                    >~CHF 1,500 - 2,000</td
                                >
                                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-400">CHF 0</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="font-bold py-3 px-4"
                                    >Investment Growth Tax</td
                                >
                                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-bold"
                                    >100% Tax Free</td
                                >
                                <td class="py-3 px-4"
                                    >Dividends & Coupons Taxed as Income</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="font-bold py-3 px-4"
                                    >Wealth Tax (Annual)</td
                                >
                                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-bold"
                                    >Exempt</td
                                >
                                <td class="py-3 px-4">Taxed as Wealth</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="font-bold py-3 px-4"
                                    >Withdrawal Tax</td
                                >
                                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-orange-600"
                                    >Reduced Capital Tax (approx 5-7%)</td
                                >
                                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-bold"
                                    >Tax Free (Capital is post-tax)</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                    <strong>Key Insight:</strong> While 3b withdrawals are tax-free,
                    the money you put into 3b has <em>already been taxed</em> at your
                    highest marginal rate. With 3a, you defer that tax and pay it
                    back decades later at a significantly reduced rate, creating a
                    massive arbitration opportunity.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- 5.4 Contribution Limits (Corrected 2026 Data) -->
            <div class="mb-16">
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                    Contribution Limits (2026/2026 Est.)
                </h3>
                <p>
                    It is vital to know your limits. Over-contributing results
                    in a refund headache and no additional tax benefit.
                </p>

                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 my-6 text-center">
                    <div
                        class="bg-white p-6 shadow-lg rounded-xl border-t-4 border-red-600"
                    >
                        <h4
                            class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide"
                        >
                            Employees & <br />Normal Earners
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-xs mb-4">
                            (Those with a 2nd Pillar / Pension Fund)
                        </p>
                        <div class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                            CHF 7,258
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-green-600 font-medium">
                            Max Annual Deduction
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div
                        class="bg-white p-6 shadow-lg rounded-xl border-t-4 border-blue-600"
                    >
                        <h4
                            class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide"
                        >
                            Self-Employed & <br />Freelancers
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-xs mb-4">
                            (Those WITHOUT a 2nd Pillar)
                        </p>
                        <div class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                            CHF 36,288
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-0">
                            Or max 20% of Net Income
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-green-600 font-medium">
                            (Whichever is lower)
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="mt-8">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">
                        FAQ: Can I catch up on missed years?
                    </h4>
                    <p>
                        <strong>For Pillar 3a:</strong> Historically, No. If you missed
                        a year, that deduction was gone forever. However, the Swiss
                        parliament has approved motion 19.3702 allowing retrospective
                        buy-ins for pillar 3a. Implementation is pending (expected
                        2025/26), but likely only for gaps occurring <em
                            >after</em
                        > the law comes into effect.
                        <br /><br />
                        <strong>For Pillar 3b:</strong> Yes, always. Since there are
                        no limits, you can invest CHF 100,000 tomorrow if you have
                        the capital.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 5.6 Side-by-Side Comparison Table -->
            <div class="mb-16">
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                    At a Glance: The Master Data Table
                </h3>
                <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                    <table
                        class="min-w-full text-sm border-collapse border border-gray-300 shadow-sm"
                    >
                        <thead>
                            <tr class="bg-gray-800 text-white">
                                <th class="p-4 text-left border border-gray-700"
                                    >Feature</th
                                >
                                <th class="p-4 text-left border border-gray-700"
                                    >Pillar 3a (Restricted)</th
                                >
                                <th class="p-4 text-left border border-gray-700"
                                    >Pillar 3b (Flexible)</th
                                >
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr class="bg-white">
                                <td class="p-4 border font-bold">Goal</td>
                                <td class="p-4 border"
                                    >Tax Optimization & Retirement</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-4 border"
                                    >Medium-term Goals & Freedom</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                                <td class="p-4 border font-bold"
                                    >Tax Deduction</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-4 border text-green-700 font-bold"
                                    >Yes (100% up to limit)</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-4 border text-red-700"
                                    >No (usually)</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-white">
                                <td class="p-4 border font-bold"
                                    >Withdrawal Age</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-4 border"
                                    >Typically 60 (M) / 59 (F) at earliest</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-4 border text-green-700 font-bold"
                                    >Any time</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                                <td class="p-4 border font-bold"
                                    >Early Access Conditions</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-4 border"
                                    >Home ownership, Leaving CH,
                                    Self-employment, Disability</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-4 border">No conditions</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-white">
                                <td class="p-4 border font-bold"
                                    >Bankruptcy Protection</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-4 border text-green-700 font-bold"
                                    >Yes (Privileged status)</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-4 border text-red-700"
                                    >No (Part of estate)</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                                <td class="p-4 border font-bold"
                                    >Insurance Integration</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-4 border"
                                    >Available (Life/Disability waivers)</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-4 border"
                                    >Available (Pure risk options)</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 5.7 Decision Tree -->
            <div>
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                    Which is Right For You?
                </h3>
                <div class="bg-blue-900 text-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-xl">
                    <ul class="space-y-6 text-lg">
                        <li class="flex gap-4">
                            <span class="font-bold text-yellow-500 text-2xl"
                                >?</span
                            >
                            <div>
                                <span class="font-bold block"
                                    >Do you want to instantly save ~20-30% in
                                    taxes on your savings?</span
                                >
                                <span class="text-blue-200 text-sm"
                                    >Yes → Always max out <strong
                                        class="text-white">Pillar 3a</strong
                                    > first.</span
                                >
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex gap-4">
                            <span class="font-bold text-yellow-500 text-2xl"
                                >?</span
                            >
                            <div>
                                <span class="font-bold block"
                                    >Are you saving for a goal 3-5 years away
                                    (e.g. Wedding, World Trip)?</span
                                >
                                <span class="text-blue-200 text-sm"
                                    >Yes → Use <strong class="text-white"
                                        >Pillar 3b</strong
                                    >. 3a funds cannot be touched for these
                                    reasons.</span
                                >
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex gap-4">
                            <span class="font-bold text-yellow-500 text-2xl"
                                >?</span
                            >
                            <div>
                                <span class="font-bold block"
                                    >Are you a high earner (CHF 120k+)?</span
                                >
                                <span class="text-blue-200 text-sm"
                                    >Yes → <strong class="text-white"
                                        >Do Both.</strong
                                    > Max your 3a limit, then pour excess savings
                                    into a flexible 3b investment plan.</span
                                >
                            </div>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
